('200003003006','(i);$$\\begin{align};  & y=\\ln \\left( 1+\\tan x \\right)\\equiv {{e}^{y}}=1+\\tan x \\\\ ; & \\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{e}^{y}} \\right]=\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ 1+\\tan x \\right] \\\\ ; && {{e}^{y}}\\frac{dy}{dx}={{\\sec }^{2}}x------(1) \\\\ ; & \\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{e}^{y}}\\frac{dy}{dx} \\right]=\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{\\sec }^{2}}x \\right] \\\\ ; & {{e}^{y}}\\frac{{{d}^{2}}y}{d{{x}^{2}}}+{{e}^{y}}{{\\left( \\frac{dy}{dx} \\right)}^{2}}=2{{\\sec }^{2}}x\\tan x--(2) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;When x = 0,;$$y=\\ln \\left( 1+\\tan 0 \\right)=0$$;$$\\begin{align};  & Eqn(1):{{e}^{0}}\\frac{dy}{dx}={{\\sec }^{2}}0\\Rightarrow \\frac{dy}{dx}=1 \\\\ ; & Eqn(2):{{e}^{0}}\\frac{{{d}^{2}}y}{d{{x}^{2}}}+{{e}^{0}}\\left( 1 \\right)=2{{\\sec }^{2}}0\\tan 0 \\\\ ; & \\frac{{{d}^{2}}y}{d{{x}^{2}}}+1=0 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\frac{{{d}^{2}}y}{d{{x}^{2}}}=-1 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii) Let $$y=f\\left( x \\right)=\\ln \\left( 1+\\tan x \\right)$$;Maclaurin\'s series for $$y = f(x)$$ is;$$\\begin{align};  & y=f\\left( 0 \\right)+f\'\\left( 0 \\right)x+\\frac{f\'\'\\left( 0 \\right)}{2!}{{x}^{2}}+... \\\\ ; & =0+\\left( 1 \\right)x+\\left( \\frac{-1}{2} \\right){{x}^{2}}+... \\\\ ; & =x-\\frac{1}{2}{{x}^{2}}+... \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;'),
