('200003003011','(i);$$\\begin{align};  & {{\\tan }^{-1}}x+{{\\tan }^{-1}}y+{{\\tan }^{-1}}\\left( xy \\right)=\\frac{7}{12}\\pi  \\\\ ; & Where \\\\ ; & x=1, \\\\ ; & {{\\tan }^{-1}}\\left( 1 \\right)+{{\\tan }^{-1}}y+{{\\tan }^{-1}}\\left[ \\left( 1 \\right)y \\right]=\\frac{7}{12}\\pi  \\\\ ; & \\frac{1}{4}\\pi +2{{\\tan }^{-1}}y=\\frac{7}{12}\\pi  \\\\ ; & 2{{\\tan }^{-1}}y=\\frac{7}{12}\\pi -\\frac{1}{4}\\pi =\\frac{1}{3}\\pi  \\\\ ; & {{\\tan }^{-1}}y=\\frac{1}{6}\\pi  \\\\ ; & \\therefore y=\\tan \\frac{1}{6}\\pi =\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii);$$\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{\\tan }^{-1}}\\left( xy \\right) \\right]=\\frac{1}{{{\\left( xy \\right)}^{2}}+1}\\left( x\\frac{dy}{dx}+y \\right)$$;;(iii);$$\\begin{align};  & \\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{\\tan }^{-1}}x+{{\\tan }^{-1}}y+{{\\tan }^{-1}}\\left( xy \\right) \\right]=\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ \\frac{7}{12}\\pi  \\right] \\\\ ; & \\frac{1}{{{x}^{2}}+1}+\\frac{1}{{{y}^{2}}+1}\\frac{dy}{dx}+\\frac{1}{{{\\left( xy \\right)}^{2}}+1}\\left( x\\frac{dy}{dx}+y \\right)=0 \\\\ ; & \\frac{1}{{{x}^{2}}+1}+\\left[ \\frac{1}{{{y}^{2}}+1}+\\frac{x}{{{\\left( xy \\right)}^{2}}+1} \\right]\\frac{dy}{dx}+\\frac{y}{{{\\left( xy \\right)}^{2}}+1}=0 \\\\ ; & When:x=1,y=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{\\left( 1 \\right)+1}+\\left[ \\frac{1}{\\left( \\frac{1}{3} \\right)+1}+\\frac{\\left( 1 \\right)}{\\left( \\frac{1}{3} \\right)+1} \\right]\\frac{dy}{dx}+\\frac{\\left( \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\right)}{\\left( \\frac{1}{3} \\right)+1}=0 \\\\ ; & \\frac{1}{2}+\\frac{3}{2}\\frac{dy}{dx}+\\frac{3}{4\\sqrt{3}}=0 \\\\ ; & \\frac{3}{2}\\frac{dy}{dx}=-\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{3}{4\\sqrt{3}} \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\frac{dy}{dx}=-\\frac{1}{3}-\\frac{1}{2\\sqrt{3}} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$'),
('200003003012','(i);$$\\begin{align};  & \\cos 3\\theta =\\cos \\left( 2\\theta +\\theta  \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\cos 2\\theta \\cos \\theta -\\sin 2\\theta \\sin \\theta  \\\\ ; & =\\left( 2{{\\cos }^{2}}\\theta -1 \\right)\\cos \\theta -\\left( 2\\sin \\theta \\cos \\theta  \\right)\\sin \\theta  \\\\ ; & =2{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -\\cos \\theta -2{{\\sin }^{2}}\\theta \\cos \\theta  \\\\ ; & =2{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -\\cos \\theta -2\\left( 1-{{\\cos }^{2}}\\theta  \\right)\\cos \\theta  \\\\ ; & =2{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -\\cos \\theta -2\\cos \\theta +2{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta  \\\\ ; & =4{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -3\\cos \\theta  \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii) With $$x=6\\cos \\theta $$;$$\\begin{align};  & {{x}^{3}}-27x+18=0 \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{\\left( 6\\cos \\theta  \\right)}^{3}}-27\\left( 6\\cos \\theta  \\right)+18=0 \\\\ ; & =216{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -162\\cos \\theta =-18 \\\\ ; & =54\\left( 4{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -3\\cos \\theta  \\right)=-18 \\\\ ; & =54\\cos 3\\theta =-18 \\\\ ; & \\cos 3\\theta =-\\frac{1}{3} \\\\ ; & 3\\theta =1.9106,2\\pi -1.9106,2\\pi +1.9106 \\\\ ; & \\theta =0.6369,1.4575,2.7313 \\\\ ; & \\therefore x=6\\cos \\theta  \\\\ ; & =4.824,0.6783,-5.502 \\\\ ; & =4.82,0.678,-5.50 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(iii) Let the substitution be $$x=a\\cos \\theta $$;$$\\begin{align};  & {{x}^{3}}-12x-2=0 \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{a}^{3}}{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -12a\\cos \\theta -2=0 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;For the substitution to be useful;$$\\begin{align};  & {{a}^{3}}{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -12a\\cos \\theta \\equiv 4{{\\cos }^{3}}\\theta -3\\cos \\theta  \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\frac{{{a}^{3}}}{12a}=\\frac{4}{3}\\Rightarrow a=\\pm 4 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;A suitable substitution is $$x=4\\cos \\theta $$;'),
('200003003013','(i) $$\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{9-{{x}^{2}}}\\equiv A+\\frac{B}{3-x}+\\frac{C}{3+x}$$;By long division,;$$\\begin{align};  & \\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{9-{{x}^{2}}}=-1+\\frac{9}{9-{{x}^{2}}}\\Rightarrow A=-1 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\frac{9}{9-{{x}^{2}}}\\equiv \\frac{9}{\\left( 3-x \\right)\\left( 3+x \\right)}\\equiv \\frac{B}{3-x}+\\frac{C}{3+x} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;Cover-up rule:;$$\\begin{align};  & x=3:B=\\frac{9}{3+3}=\\frac{3}{2} \\\\ ; & x=-3:C=\\frac{9}{3-\\left( -3 \\right)}=\\frac{3}{2} \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{9-{{x}^{2}}}\\equiv -1+\\frac{3}{2\\left( 3-x \\right)}+\\frac{3}{2\\left( 3+x \\right)} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii);$$\\begin{align};  & \\int_{0}^{2}{\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{9-{{x}^{2}}}dx} \\\\ ; & =\\int_{0}^{2}{\\left( -1+\\frac{9}{{{3}^{2}}-{{x}^{2}}} \\right)dx} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ -x+\\frac{9}{2\\left( 3 \\right)}\\ln \\left( \\frac{3+x}{3-x} \\right) \\right]_{0}^{2} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ \\left( -2+\\frac{3}{2}\\ln 5 \\right)-\\left( 0+\\frac{3}{2}\\ln 1 \\right) \\right] \\\\ ; & =\\frac{3}{2}\\ln 5-2 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(iii);$$\\begin{align};  & \\int_{0}^{2}{\\ln \\left( 9-{{x}^{2}} \\right)dx} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ \\ln \\left( 9-{{x}^{2}} \\right)\\left( x \\right) \\right]_{0}^{2}-\\int_{0}^{2}{x\\frac{\\left( -2x \\right)}{9-{{x}^{2}}}dx} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ \\ln \\left( 9-{{2}^{2}} \\right)\\left( 2 \\right)-0 \\right]+2\\int_{0}^{2}{\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{9-{{x}^{2}}}dx} \\\\ ; & =2\\ln 5+2\\left( \\frac{3}{2}\\ln 5-2 \\right)=5\\ln 5-4 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;'),
