('200004003008','(i);Let n = no. of tickets Charlie has = 20;Let p = P(win a prize) = 10% + 0.1% = 0.101 and;q = 1- p = 0.899;Let X = no. of tickets out of n that win a prize ;$$X \\sim B(n,p)$$;;(a) P(he wins at least 1 prize);$$= P ( X \\geq 1 ) \\equiv 1 - P ( X = 0 )$$ ;$$= 1 - q^n = 1 - (0.899)^{20}$$;$$= 0.8811 = 0.881$$ (ans);;(b) P(he wins at most 3 prizes);$$= P ( X \\leq 3 )$$ ;$$= P(X = 0) + P(X = 1) + P(X = 2) + P(X = 3)$$ ;$$= q^n + {}^{n}{C}_{1} p^1 q^{n - 1} + {}^{n}{C}_{2} p^2 q^{n - 2} + {}^{n}{C}_{3} p^3 q^{n - 3}$$ ;$$= (0.899)^{20} + {}^{20}{C}_{1}(0.101)(0.899)^{19} + {}^{20}{C}_{2}( 0.101 )^2 ( 0.899 )^{18} + {}^{20}{C}_{P3} ( 0.101 )^3 ( 0.899 )^{17}$$ ;$$= 0.8634 = 0.863$$ (ans);;(ii) ;Let $${n}_{m}$$ = no. of tickets Mary has = 400;(a) Let $${p}_{s}$$ = P(win a small prize) = 10% = 0.1;and $${q}_{s}$$ = 1 - $${p}_{s}$$ = 0.9;Let Y = no. of small prizes Mary wins;$$Y \\sim B({n}_{m} , {p}_{s})$$;Since $${n}_{m}$$ (=400) is large, $${n}_{m}{p}_{s}$$ = 40 > 5 and $${n}_{m}{q}_{s}$$ = 360 >5,;$$Y \\sim N({n}_{m}{p}_{s} , {n}_{m}{p}_{s})$$ approximately;;$$P ( Y \\leq 35 )$$ ;$$= P(Y < 35.5)$$   $$\\gets $$ continuity correction;$$\\equiv P ( Z < \\frac{35.5 - {n}_{m}{p}_{s}}{\\sqrt{{n}_{m}{p}_{s}{q}_{s}}} )$$ ;$$= P(Z < \\frac{35.5 - 400(0.1)}{\\sqrt{400(0.1)(0.9)}})$$ ;$$= P ( Z < - 0.75 ) \\equiv 1 - \\Phi ( 0.75 )$$ ;$$= 1 - 0.7734 = 0.2266 = 0.227$$ (ans);;(b) Let $${p}_{l}$$ = P(win a large prize) = 0.1% = 0.001;Let L = no. of large prizes Mary wins;$$L \\sim B({n}_{m},{p}_{l})$$;Since $${n}_{m}$$ ( = 400) is large and $${n}_{m}{p}_{l} = 0.4 < 5$$,;$$L \\sim {P}_{o}(\\lambda)$$ approximately,;                                 where $$\\lambda= {n}_{m}{p}_{l} = 0.4$$;$$P ( L \\leq 2 ) = P ( L = 0 ) + P ( L = 1 ) + P ( L = 2 )$$ ;$$ = e^{- \\lambda}[ \\frac{\\lambda^0}{0 !}+ \\frac{\\lambda^1}{1 !}+ \\frac{\\lambda^2}{2 !}]$$ ;$$ = e^{- 0.4} [ 1 + 0.4 + \\frac{( 0.4 )^2}{2} ]$$ ;$$ = 0.9921 = 0.992 $$ (ans)'),
('200004003009','(i) Let F = mass of fruit in a tin;Let $${\\mu}_{F} = E(F) = 278$$g;Let $${{\\sigma}_{F}}^2 = Var(F) = (9.2)^2 g^2$$;Let T = mass of fruit and juice in a tin;Let $${\\mu}_{T}$$ = E(T) = 432 g;Let $${{\\sigma}_{T}}^2 = Var(T) = (7.8)^2 g^2$$;;Let J = mass of juice in a tin = T - F;Let $${\\mu}_{J} = E(J) = E(T - F) = E(T) - E(F)$$;$$= 432 - 278 = 154$$;Let $${{\\sigma}_{J}}^2 = Var(J) = Var(T - F) = Var(T) + Var(F)$$;              $$= (9.2)^2 + (7.8)^2 = 145.48 g^2$$; ;$$J \\sim N ( {\\mu}_{J} , {{\\sigma}_{J}}^2 );$$[P(J > 170) ;$$\\equiv P ( Z > \\frac{170 - {\\mu}_{J}}{{\\sigma}_{J}} ) = P ( Z > \\frac{170 - 154}{\\sqrt{145.48}} )$$ ;$$= P(Z > 1.3265) = 1 - \\Phi (1.327)$$;$$= 1 - 0.9077 = 0.0923$$ (ans);;(ii)  ;$$X = {F}_{1} + {F}_{2} + {F}_{3} + {F}_{4}$$ ;$${\\mu}_{X} = E(X) = E({F}_{1} + {F}_{2} + {F}_{3} + {F}_{4})$$ ;$$= 4E ( F ) = 4 ( 278 ) = 1112$$ g ; ;$${{\\sigma}_{X}}^2 = Var(X) = Var({F}_{1} + {F}_{2} + {F}_{3} + {F}_{4})$$ ;$$ = 4Var ( F ) = 4 ( 9.2 )^2 = 338.56 g^2$$ ;;$$ X \\sim N({\\mu}_{X}, {{\\sigma}_{X}}^2)$$ ;P ( X < 1112 ) ;$$ \\equiv P(Z < \\frac{1112 - {\\mu}_{X}}{{\\sigma}_{X}})$$ ;$$ = P ( Z < \\frac{1112 - 1112}{\\sqrt{338.56}} )$$ ;$$ = P(Z < 0) \\equiv \\Phi(0) = 0.5$$ (ans);;$$\\overline{x} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n} = \\frac{748}{15} = 49.867$$ g ;$${\\hat{\\sigma}}^2 = \\frac{1}{n - 1}[ \\sum x^2 - \\frac{1}{n}(\\sum x)^2 ]$$ ;$$ = \\frac{1}{14} [ 56243 - \\frac{1}{15} ( 748 )^2  = 1353.052$$;;$${z}_{0.10}\\sqrt{\\frac{{\\hat{\\sigma}}^2}{n}} = 1.282 \\sqrt{\\frac{1353.052}{15}}= 12.176$$;;A symmetric 80% confidence interval for the mean sugar content in a tin;$$=[ \\overline{x} - {z}_{0.10} \\sqrt{\\frac{{\\hat{\\sigma}}^2}{n}} , \\overline{x} - {z}_{0.10} \\sqrt{\\frac{{\\hat{\\sigma}}^2}{n}} ]$$ ;$$ = [ 49.867 - 12.176, 49.867 + 12.176 ]$$ ;$$ = [ 37.69 , 62.04 ] = [ 37.7 , 62.0 ]$$ (ans)'),
('200004003010','(a) Let n = no, of observations = 50;Let $${\\mu}_{0}$$ = assumed mean = 22;Let $$\\sigma$$ = Var(X) = 36;Test $${H}_{0}$$ : $${\\mu}$$ =  $${\\mu}_{0}$$ against $${H}_{1}$$ : $${\\mu}$$ < $${\\mu}_{0}$$ ;a 1-tailed test for less;;The 1% critical value, $${z}_{0.01} = 2.326$$;Reject $${H}_{0}$$ if $$z < -{z}_{0.01}$$;Under $${H}_{0}$$ , the test statistic is ;$$z = \\frac{\\overline{x} - {\\mu}_{0}}{\\sigma / \\sqrt{n}} = \\frac{20.2 - 22}{\\sqrt{36 / 50}} = - 2.121$$;;Since $$z > - {z}_{0.01}$$, do not reject $${H}_{0}$$ and conclude that, at the 1% level of significance there is insufficient evidence that the mean $${\\mu}$$ is less than 22.;;(b) Let p = proportion of the population who know the leader\'s name;Let $${n}_{1}$$ = sample size = 850;$$\\hat{p} = \\frac{124}{850} = \\frac{62}{425}$$ ;$$\\hat{q} = \\frac{363}{425}$$ ;;$${z}_{0.025} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p} \\hat{q}}{{n}_{1}}} = 1.960\\sqrt{\\frac{( \\frac{62}{425} ) ( \\frac{363}{425} )}{850}} = 0.02373$$;;The 95% confidence interval for p is;$$[ \\hat{p} - {z}_{0.025} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p} \\hat{q}}{{n}_{1}}} , \\hat{p} + {z}_{0.025} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p} \\hat{q}}{{n}_{1}}} ]$$ ;$$ = [ \\frac{62}{425} - 0.02373, \\frac{62}{425}+ 0.02373 ]$$;$$ = [ 0.1222 , 0.1696 ]$$ ;$$ = [ 0.122, 0.170 ]$$ (ans);;Let $${n}_{2}$$ = sample size = 953;Let $${p}_{0}$$ = assumed p = 0.25;$$\\hat{p} = \\frac{263}{953}$$;Test $${H}_{0}$$ : $$p = {p}_{0}$$ against $${H}_{1}$$ : $$p > {p}_{0}$$;a 1-tailed test for more;The 5% critical value, $${z}_{0.05} = 1.645$$;Reject $${H}_{0}$$ if $$z > {z}_{0.05}$$;Under $${H}_{0}$$, the test statistic is ;$$z = \\frac{\\hat{p} - {p}_{0}}{\\sqrt{{p}_{0}{q}_{0} / {n}_{2}}} = \\frac{\\frac{263}{953} - 0.25}{\\sqrt{( 0.25 ) ( 0.75 ) / 953}} = 1.852$$;;Since $$z > {z}_{0.05}$$, reject $${H}_{0}$$ and conclude that, at the 5% level of significance, there is sufficient evidence that p > 0.25. (ans)'),
('200004003011','Let B = a black die taken;Let R= a red ball taken;Let G = a green ball taken;;The probability tree is displayed:;img;;Probability of event M is happening given that event W was happened,;$$P( M|W ) = \\frac{P(M \\cap W)}{P(W)} = \\frac{ P( WRG ) + P( WGR )}{P(W)}$$;$$ = \\frac{\\frac{3}{28} + \\frac{3}{28}}{\\frac{2}{5}} = \\frac{15}{28}$$  (ans);;(i) $$P( M \\cap W ) = P( WRG ) + P( WGR )$$;$$=\\frac{3}{28} + \\frac{3}{28} = \\frac{3}{14}$$ (ans);;(ii) $$P( W|M ) = \\frac{P( W \\cap M)}{P(M)} = \\frac{ P( WRG ) + P( WGR )}{P( WRG )+ P ( WGR ) + P( BRG ) + P( BGR ) }$$;$$ = \\frac{\\frac{3}{28} + \\frac{3}{28}}{\\frac{3}{28} + \\frac{3}{28} + \\frac{6}{35} + \\frac{6}{35}} = \\frac{15}{13}$$  (ans);;(iii) $$P( W \\cup M )$$;$$ = P( W ) + P( BRG ) + P( BGR )$$;$$ = \\frac{2}{5} + \\frac{6}{35} + \\frac{6}{35} = \\frac{26}{35}$$ (ans);;In the container there are 20 objects comprising 2 white dice, 3 black dice, 9 red balls, and 6 green balls.;There are $$4!$$ ways to select the 4 objects.;$$\\therefore$$ P( one object of each colour taken);$$= 4! \\times \\frac{2}{20} \\times \\frac{3}{20} \\times \\frac{9}{20} \\times \\frac{6}{20} = \\frac{243}{5000}$$ (ans)'),
('200004003012','(i) Sketch $$y = x( x^2  - 4 )$$;At $$y = 0$$ , $$x = 0$$ , $$\\pm 2$$;;(ii) Sketch $$y = \\frac{x + 1}{(x - 1)^2}$$;As $$x \\to 1$$ , $$y \\to \\infty$$  $$\\Rightarrow x = 1$$ is an asymptote;As $$x \\to \\infty$$ , $$y \\to 0$$  $$\\Rightarrow y = 0$$ is an asymptote;At $$x = 0$$ , $$y = 1$$; at $$y = 0$$ , $$x = -1$$;;img;;$$x( x^2  - 4 ) = \\frac{x + 1}{(x - 1)^2}$$;$$\\equiv x ( x^2 - 4)( x-1 )^2 = x + 1$$;$$\\equiv ( x^3 - 4x ) (x-1)^2 - ( x+ 1 ) = 0$$;Let $$f(x) = ( x^3 - 4x ) (x-1)^2 - ( x+ 1 )$$;Let $$\\alpha$$ denotes the root of $$f(x) = 0$$ in [ -1, 0];;$$f( -1 ) = \\left[( -1 )^3 - 4( -1 )\\right]\\left[-1 -1\\right]^2 - \\left[ -1 + 1\\right] = 12$$;$$f( 0 ) = \\left[( 0 )^3 - 4( 0 )\\right]\\left[0 -1\\right]^2 - \\left[ 0 + 1\\right] = -1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\alpha \\in \\left[ -1, 0\\right]$$;;Linear interpolation on [ -1, 0]:;$$\\alpha \\approx \\frac{(-1)| f(0) | + (0)| f(-1) |}{| f(0) | + | f(-1)|}$$;$$=\\frac{(-1)| -1 | + (0)| 12 |}{| -1 | + | 12 |}$$;$$= - 0.07692 = - 0.0769$$ (ans);;$$f\'(x) = \\frac{d}{dx}\\left[( x^3 - 4x ) (x-1)^2 - ( x+ 1 ) \\right]$$;       $$=(3{x}^{2} - 4)( x - 1 )^2 + ( x^3 - 4x )2( x - 1) - 1$$;Newton-Raphson method:;with $${x}_{0} = 2$$,;$$f({x}_{0}) = \\left[2^3 - 4(2)\\right]\\left[2 - 1\\right]^2 - \\left[2 + 1\\right] = - 3$$;$$f\'({x}_{0}) = \\left[(3(2)^2 - 4)( 2 - 1 )^2 + (2^3 - 4(2))2(2 - 1)\\right] - 1 = 7$$;;$${x}_{1} = {x}_{0} - f({x}_{0})/f\'({x}_{0})$$;            $$= 2 - ( -3 ) / ( 7 )$$;            $$= 2.429 = 2.43$$ (ans)'),
('200004003013','(a)$$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2x + 2x{y}^{2} = 2x ( 1 + y^2 )$$;$$\\int \\frac{dy}{1 + y^2 } = \\int 2xdx$$;$${\\tan }^{-1} y = {x}^{2} + c$$, c = constant;$$\\therefore y = \\tan (x^2 + c)$$;When $$x = 0$$ , $$y = 1$$;$$\\Rightarrow 1 = \\tan ( 0 + c )$$   $$\\Rightarrow c = \\frac{1}{4}\\pi$$;$$\\therefore y = \\tan (x^2 + \\frac{1}{4}\\pi )$$ (ans);;(b) $$( 1 + x^2 )\\frac{dy}{dx} + 4xy = \\frac{4x}{( 1 + x^2  )^3}$$;$$\\equiv \\frac{dy}{dx} + \\frac{4x}{( 1 + x^2 )}y = \\frac{4x}{( 1 + x^2  )^4}$$;Let $$h(x) = \\int \\frac{4x}{( 1 + x^2 )}dx$$;             $$= 2 ln( 1 + x^2 ) = ln( 1 + x^2 )^2$$;$$\\Rightarrow$$ integrating factor;$${e}^{h(x)} = {e}^{ln( 1 + x^2 )^2} = ( 1 + x^2 )^2$$ and;$${e}^{-h(x)} = {e}^{-ln( 1 + x^2 )^2} = \\frac{1}{( 1 + x^2 )^2}$$;;$$\\therefore$$ General solution is;$$y = {e}^{-h(x)}\\left[\\int {e}^{hx} \\frac{4x}{(1 + x^2)^4}dx + c\\right]$$, c = constant;   $$= \\frac{1}{( 1 + x^2 )^2}\\left[\\int ( 1 + x^2 )^2 \\frac{4x}{(1 + x^2)^4}dx + c\\right]$$;   $$= \\frac{1}{( 1 + x^2 )^2}\\left[\\int \\frac{4x}{(1 + x^2)^2}dx + c\\right]$$;   $$= \\frac{1}{( 1 + x^2 )^2}\\left[ - \\frac{2}{(1 + x^2)} + c\\right] = \\frac{c(1 + x^2) - 2}{(1 + x^2)^3}$$;When $$x = 0$$ , $$y = 1$$;$$\\Rightarrow 1 =  \\frac{c(1 + 0^2) - 2}{(1 + 0^2)^3}$$  $$\\Rightarrow c = 3$$;$$\\therefore y = \\frac{3(1 + x^2) - 2}{(1 + x^2)^3} = \\frac{3{x}^{2} + 1}{(1 + x^2)^3}$$ (ans)'),
