('200203003010',';$$\\begin{align};  & x={{t}^{2}},y={{t}^{3}} \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\frac{dy}{dx}=\\frac{dy}{dt}/\\frac{dx}{dt}=\\frac{d}{dt}\\left[ {{t}^{3}} \\right]/\\frac{d}{dt}\\left[ {{t}^{2}} \\right] \\\\ ; & =\\frac{3{{t}^{2}}}{2t}=\\frac{3}{2}t \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;At the point with the parameter t, equation of a tangent is;$$\\begin{align};  & y-\\left( {{t}^{3}} \\right)=\\frac{3}{2}t\\left[ x-\\left( {{t}^{2}} \\right) \\right] \\\\ ; & 2y-2{{t}^{3}}=3tx-3{{t}^{3}} \\\\ ; & \\therefore 2y-3tx+{{t}^{3}}=0 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(i) Tangent passes through fixed point (X, Y);$$\\Rightarrow 2Y-3tX+{{t}^{3}}=0$$, which is a cubic equation in the parameter t;$$\\Rightarrow$$ there cannot be more than 3 real roots t;$$\\Rightarrow$$ there cannot be more than 3 tangents passing through (X, Y);;(ii) At the point where t=2, equation of tangent is;$$\\begin{align};  & 2y-3\\left( 2 \\right)x+{{2}^{3}}=0 \\\\ ; & y-3x+4=0 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;The tangent meets curve at t=u, i.e. the point $$\\left( {{u}^{2}},{{u}^{3}} \\right)$$;$$\\begin{align};  & \\Rightarrow {{u}^{3}}-3{{u}^{2}}+4=0 \\\\ ; & \\left( u+1 \\right)\\left( {{u}^{2}}-4u+4 \\right)=0 \\\\ ; & \\left( u+1 \\right){{\\left( u-2 \\right)}^{2}}=0 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;$$u=-1$$ or $$u=2$$ (the tangent);$$\\therefore u=-1$$'),
('200203003011','$$f\\left( x \\right)=\\frac{{{x}^{3}}+2}{{{x}^{2}}-1}\\equiv x+\\frac{x+2}{{{x}^{2}}-1}\\equiv x=\\frac{x+2}{\\left( x+1 \\right)\\left( x-1 \\right)}$$;Let $$\\frac{x+2}{\\left( x+1 \\right)\\left( x-1 \\right)}=\\frac{A}{x+1}+\\frac{B}{x-1}$$;Clearing the fractions:;$$x+2=A\\left( x-1 \\right)+B\\left( x+1 \\right)$$;Cover-up rule:;$$\\begin{align};  & x=-1:A=\\frac{\\left( -1 \\right)+2}{\\left( -1 \\right)-1}=-\\frac{1}{2} \\\\ ; & x=1:B=\\frac{\\left( 1 \\right)+2}{\\left( 1 \\right)+1}=\\frac{3}{2} \\\\ ; & \\therefore f\\left( x \\right)\\equiv x-\\frac{1}{2\\left( x+1 \\right)}+\\frac{3}{2\\left( x-1 \\right)} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;$$\\begin{align};  & \\int\\limits_{-4}^{-2}{f\\left( x \\right)dx} \\\\ ; & \\equiv \\int\\limits_{-4}^{-2}{\\left[ x-\\frac{1}{2\\left( x+1 \\right)}+\\frac{3}{2\\left( x-1 \\right)} \\right]dx} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ \\frac{1}{2}{{x}^{2}}-\\frac{1}{2}\\ln \\left| x+1 \\right|+\\frac{3}{2}\\ln \\left| x-1 \\right| \\right]_{-4}^{-2} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{2}\\left[ {{x}^{2}}-\\ln \\left| x+1 \\right|+3\\ln \\left| x-1 \\right| \\right]_{-4}^{-2} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{2}\\left[ {{\\left( -2 \\right)}^{2}}-\\ln \\left| -2+1 \\right|+3\\ln \\left| -2-1 \\right| \\right]-\\frac{1}{2}\\left[ {{\\left( -4 \\right)}^{2}}-\\ln \\left| -4+1 \\right|+3\\ln \\left| -4-1 \\right| \\right] \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{2}\\left[ 4-\\ln 1+3\\ln 3 \\right]-\\frac{1}{2}\\left[ 16-\\ln 3+3\\ln 5 \\right] \\\\ ; & =-6.2169=-6.22\\left( 3sf \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;'),
('200203003012','Let $$P_n$$ denotes;$$\\begin{align};  & \\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{n}{\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)}}=\\frac{n\\left( n+3 \\right)}{4\\left( n+1 \\right)\\left( n+2 \\right)} \\\\ ; & n=1, \\\\ ; & LHS=\\frac{1}{1\\left( 1+1 \\right)\\left( 1+2 \\right)}=\\frac{1}{6} \\\\ ; & RHS=\\frac{1\\left( 1+3 \\right)}{4\\left( 1+1 \\right)\\left( 1+2 \\right)}=\\frac{1}{6}=LHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;$$\\therefore P_1$$ is true;Assume $$P_k$$ is true for $$k\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$,;i.e. $$\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{n}{\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)}}=\\frac{k\\left( k+3 \\right)}{4\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)}$$;For n=k+1,;$$\\begin{align};  & RHS=\\frac{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+3 \\right]}{4\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+1 \\right]\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+2 \\right]} \\\\ ; & LHS=\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{k+1}{\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)}} \\\\ ; & =\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{k}{\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)}}+\\frac{1}{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+1 \\right]\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+2 \\right]} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{k\\left( k+3 \\right)}{4\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)}+\\frac{1}{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{k\\left( k+3 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)+4}{4\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{{{k}^{3}}+6{{k}^{2}}+9k+4}{4\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( {{k}^{2}}+5k+4 \\right)}{4\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{{{k}^{2}}+5k+4}{4\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)}=\\frac{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+4 \\right)}{4\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( k+3 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\frac{\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+3 \\right]}{4\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+1 \\right]\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+2 \\right]}=RHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;$$P_{k+1}$$ is true if $$P_k$$ is true.;Therefore, by mathematical induction, $$P_n$$ is true for all $$n\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$;;For all $$n\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$,;$$\\begin{align};  & {{n}^{2}}+3n<{{n}^{2}}+3n+2 \\\\ ; & \\equiv n\\left( n+3 \\right)<\\left( n+1 \\right)\\left( n+2 \\right) \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\frac{n\\left( n+3 \\right)}{\\left( n+1 \\right)\\left( n+2 \\right)}<1 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\frac{n\\left( n+3 \\right)}{4\\left( n+1 \\right)\\left( n+2 \\right)}<\\frac{1}{4} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;For all $$r\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$,;$$\\begin{align};  & 3r+1>2r \\\\ ; & {{r}^{3}}+3{{r}^{2}}+3r+1>{{r}^{3}}+3{{r}^{2}}+2r \\\\ ; & {{\\left( r+1 \\right)}^{3}}>r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right) \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{{{\\left( r+1 \\right)}^{3}}}<\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)} \\\\ ; & \\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{n}{\\frac{1}{{{\\left( r+1 \\right)}^{3}}}}<\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{n}{\\frac{1}{r\\left( r+1 \\right)\\left( r+2 \\right)}} \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{n}{\\frac{1}{{{\\left( r+1 \\right)}^{3}}}}<\\frac{n\\left( n+3 \\right)}{4\\left( n+1 \\right)\\left( n+2 \\right)}<\\frac{1}{4} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$'),
