('200503003006','Let $$P_n$$ denotes;$$\\begin{align}\\sum^{n}_{r=1} \\frac{3r+1}{r(r+1)(r+2)} = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6n+7}{2(n+1)(n+2)}\\end{align}$$;;For n=1, ;$$\\begin{align};LHS = \\sum_{r}^{1}\\frac{3r+1}{r\\left ( r+ 1 \\right )\\left ( r+2 \\right )} = \\frac{3+1}{(1)\\left [(1)+ 1 \\right]\\left [(1)+2 \\right]} = \\frac{2}{3}\\\\;RHS = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6(1)+7}{2[(1)+1][(1)+2]} = \\frac{2}{3} = LHS;\\end{align}$$;$$\\therefore P_1$$ is true;;Assume $$P_1$$ is true for $$k \\in \\mathbb{Z}^{+}$$,;i.e. $$\\begin{align}\\sum^k_{r = 1} \\frac{3r + 1}{r( r + 1 ) ( r + 2 )} = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6k + 7}{2(k + 1 ) ( k + 2 )}\\end{align}$$;;For n = k + 1;$$\\begin{align};& RHS = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6(k+1) + 7}{2( k + 1 +1)(k + 1 + 2)};= \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6k + 13}{2( k + 2 ) ( k + 3)} \\\\;;&LHS =  \\sum^k_{r = 1} \\frac{3r + 1}{r( r + 1 ) ( r + 2 )}\\\\;&= \\sum^k_{r = 1} \\frac{3r + 1}{r( r + 1 ) ( r + 2 )} + \\frac{3 ( k +1) + 1 } { ( k+1) [(k+1)+1][(k+1)+2]} \\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6k+7}{2(k+1)(k+2)} + \\frac{3k+4}{(k+1)(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{(k+3)(6k+7) - 2(3k+4)}{2(k+1)(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6k^{2} + 25k +21 - 6k - 8}{2(k+1)(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{6k^{2} + 19k + 13}{2(k+1)(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{(k+1)(6k+13)}{2(k+1)(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{(6k+13)}{2(k+2)(k+3)}\\\\;& = \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{(6(k+1)+7)}{2(k+1+1)(k+1+2)} = RHS\\\\;\\end{align}$$;$$\\therefore P_{k+1}$$ is true if $$P_{k}$$ is true;Therefore, by mathematical induction, $$P_{n}$$ is true for all $$n \\in \\mathbb{Z}^{+}$$'),
