('19980300104', '199803001', 4, 'A curve has the equation \\[y=\\frac{6}{(1-2x)}\\] Find an expression for \\[\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}\\] ;(i) Hence find the equation of the normal to the curve at the point where x = 2.;(ii) Hence find the approximate increase in y as x increases from 2 to 2 + p, where p is small.', 48, 4801, 1, 'Exam Paper',0),
