('19990100113', '199901001', 13, 'img;(a) The diagram shows part of the curve \\[y=\\frac{1}{x}\\] The shaded region is bounded by the curve, the x-axis and the lines x = 1 and x = k. Given that the volume of the solid of revolution, obtained by rotating the shaded region through  \\[360^{\\circ}\\]   about the x-axis, is \\[\\frac{\\pi}{6}units^3\\] evaluate k.;img;(b) The diagram shows part of the curve \\[y=9-x^2\\] The points P and Q lie on the curve and have x-coordinates 1 and 3 respectively. The line PQ divides the area between the curve and the positive axes into two regions, A and B . Show that the area of A is 12.5 times the area of B .', 49, 4903, 3, 'Exam Paper',0),
