('20030300104', '200303001', 4, 'A rectangular block has a square base. The length of each side of the base is $$(\\sqrt3-\\sqrt2)$$ m and the volume of the block is $$4(\\sqrt2-3\\sqrt3)m^3$$. Find, without using a calculator, the height of the block in the form $$(a\\sqrt2+b\\sqrt3)$$m, where a and b are integers.', 38, 3802, 1, 'Exam Paper',0),
