('20060400110', '200604001', 10, '(a)	How many different four-digit numbers can be formed from the digits 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9 if no digit may be repeated?;(b)	In a group of 13 entertainers, 8 are singers and 5 are comedians. A concert is to be given by 5 of these entertainers. In the concert there must be at least 1 comedian and there must be more singers than comedians. Find the number of different ways that the 5 entertainers can be selected.', 55, 5501, 4, 'Exam Paper',0),
