('20060400112', '200604001', 12, 'img;The diagram shows an isoceles triangle ABC in which A is the point(3, 3), B is the point(6, 3) and C lies below the x- axis. Given that the area of triangle ABC is 6 square units,;i) Find the coordinates of C.;The line CB is extended to the point D so that B is the mid- point of CD.;ii) Find the coordinates of D.;A line is drawn from D, parallel to AC, to the point E(10, k) and C is joined to E.;iii) Find the value of k.;iv) Prove that angle CED is not a right angle.', 47, 4701, 7, 'Exam Paper',0),
