('20070300105', '200703001', 5, '(i) Differentiate $$\\ln(\\sin (x))$$with respect to x.;img;(ii) The diagram shows part of the curve $$y=\\cot (x)$$, cutting the x-axis at$$(\\frac{\\pi}{2}, 0)$$. The line $$y=\\sqrt3$$ intersects the curve at P. A line is drawn from P, parallel to the y-axis, to meet x-axis at Q. Use your result from part (i) to find the area of the shaded region.', 49, 4903, 1, 'Exam Paper',0),
