('20070400108', '200704001', 8, '(a)	Each of seven cards has on it one of the digits 1,2,3,4,5,6,7; no two cards have the same digit. Four of these cards are selected and arranges to form a 4-digit number.;(i)	How many different 4-digit numbers can be formed in this way?;(ii)	How many of these 4-digit numbers begin and end with an even digit?;(b)	4 people are selected to form a debating team from a group of 5 men and 2 women.;(i)	Find the number of possible teams that can be selected.;(ii)	How many of these contain at least 1 woman?', 55, 5501, 3, 'Exam Paper',0),
