('20080300106', '200803001', 6, 'A cyclist starts from rest from a point A and travels in a straight line until he comes to a rest at a point B . During the motion, his velocity, $$v ms^{-1}$$, is given by $$v = 6t-\\frac{1}{2}t^2$$, where t is the time in seconds after leaving A . ;Find;(i) the time taken for the cyclist to travel from A to B,;(ii) the distance AB,;(iii) the acceleration of the cyclist when t = 8.', 49, 4903, 1, 'Exam Paper',0),
