('20080400107', '200804001', 7, 'The function f is defined by $$f(x) = 4\\cos  2x -2$$;(i) State the amplitude of f.;(ii) State the period of f.;The equation of a curve is $$y = 4\\cos 2x-2$$ for $$0^{\\circ} \\leq x \\leq 180^{\\circ} $$.;(iii) Find the coordinates of the minimum point of the curve.;(iv) Find the coordinates of the points where the curve meets the x-axis.;(v) Sketch the graph of $$y = 4\\cos 2x-2$$ for $$0^{\\circ}  \\leq x \\leq 180^{\\circ} $$.;(vi) Sketch the graph of $$y =|4\\cos 2x-2|$$ for $$0^{\\circ}  \\leq x \\leq 180^{\\circ} $$.', 45, 4502, 3, 'Exam Paper',0),
