('19950100101','i) \\[f^{2}\\left ( 4 \\right )\\]	\\[ =f\\left ( f\\left ( 4 \\right ) \\right )\\];\\[=\\left ( \\frac{\\left ( 3\\left ( 4 \\right ) \\right )}{\\left ( 4+2 \\right )} \\right )\\];;\\[= f\\left ( 2 \\right )\\];\\[=\\left ( \\frac{\\left ( 3\\left ( 2 \\right ) \\right )}{\\left ( 2+2 \\right )} \\right )\\];\\[= \\frac{3}{2}\\] (ANS);ii) Let \\[y= \\frac{\\left ( 3x \\right )}{\\left ( x+2 \\right )}\\];\\[xy+2y= 3x\\];\\[x\\left ( y-3 \\right )=-2y\\] ;\\[x=\\frac{\\left (2y  \\right )}{\\left (3-y  \\right )}\\];\\[f^{ -1 }:x \\mapsto \\frac{\\left ( 2x \\right )}{\\left ( 3-x \\right )},x\\neq 3 \\](ANS);'),
('19950100102','$$y=6-(x-2)^4$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = -4(x-2)^3$$;When $$x = 1$$, ;$$y = 6-(1-2)^4=5$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = -4(1-2)^3=4$$;Gradient at normal at (1, 5) = $$-\\frac{1}{4}$$;Equation of normal at (1, 5): ;$$ \\frac{(y-5)}{(x-1)}= -\\frac{1}{4}$$;$$4y-20 = -x+1$$;$$4y+x = 21$$;'),
('19950100103','$$y+4 = x$$ (1);$$y^2+17 = 2x^2$$ (2); From (1): $$y =x - 4$$;Substitute into (2):;$$(x-4)^2+17 = 2x^2$$; $$x^2-8x+16+17=2x^2$$;$$x^2+8x-33=0$$;$$(x+11)(x-3)=0$$;x = -11 or 3 respectively;y= -15 or -1 respectively;The solutions are (-11, -15) and (3, -1).'),
('19950100104','Coordinates of M = $$\\frac{(-1+3)}{2},\\frac{(10+2)}{2}= (1,6)$$; AM = $$\\sqrt{(5-1)^2+(8-6)^2}$$;= $$\\sqrt{20}$$ (ANS);Gradient of AM = $$\\frac{(8-6)}{(5-1)}= \\frac{2}{4}= \\frac{1}{2}$$;		       Gradient of AC = $$\\frac{(10-2)}{(-1-3)} = \\frac{8}{-4}= -2$$;since the products of the gradients is - 1, the lines are perpendicular,(shown);Area of triangle ABC = $$\\frac{1}{2} (AM)(BC)$$  = $$\\frac{1}{2} (\\sqrt {20})(\\sqrt{(-1-3)^2+(10-2)^2)}$$;= $$\\frac{1}{2} (\\sqrt {20})(\\sqrt{80})$$;= $$\\frac{1}{2} (\\sqrt {1600})$$;= $$\\frac{1}{2} (40)$$;= 20 (ANS)   '),
('19950100105','$$(\\cot A-\\tan A)\\cos A$$= $$(\\frac{\\cos A}{\\sin A} - \\frac{\\sin A}{\\cos A})\\cos A$$;= $$\\frac{(\\cos ^2A)}{\\sin A} - \\sin A$$;= $$\\frac{(1-\\sin ^2A)}{(\\sin A)}-\\sin A$$;= $$\\csc A - \\sin A - \\sin A$$;= $$\\csc A - 2\\sin A$$ (Proved)'),
('19950100106','a = coefficient of $$x^2$$;    = $$\\binom{20}{2}3^18$$;b = coefficient of $$x^3$$;   = $$\\binom{20}{2}3^17$$;  $$\\frac{a}{b} = (\\binom{20}{2}3^18) / (\\binom{20}{2}3^17) ;= \\frac{\\frac{(20!)}{(2!18!)(3)}}{\\frac{(20!)}{(17!(3)}};= 3(\\frac{(3!17!)}{(2!18!)})$$;= $$3(\\frac{3}{18})$$;= $$(\\frac{1}{2})$$'),
('19950100107','i)	   $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 3 + \\frac{4}{x^{2}}$$ (Ans);	ii)	$$\\frac{\\delta y}{\\delta x} \\approx  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}$$; $$\\delta y \\approx  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} \\delta x = (3+\\frac{4}{x^{2}})\\delta x$$;When $$x = 2$$ and $$\\delta x = p$$,;$$\\delta y \\approx (3+\\frac{4}{4})p = 4p$$'),
('19950100108','a)$$x(x+5) \\geq -6$$;$$x^2+5x+6 \\geq 0$$; $$(x+2)(x+3) \\geq 0$$;img;From the graph, $$x \\leq 3$$ or $$x \\geq -2$$ (Ans);b) $$y = c - 3x$$ (1);     $$xy = 3$$      (2);Substitute (1) into (2):;$$x(c - 3x) = 3$$;$$cx - 3x^2 = 3$$;$$3x^2 - cx +3 = 0$$;Discriminant <0;$$-(c)^2 - 4(3)(3) < 0$$;$$c^2 < 36$$;$$-6 < c < 6$$'),
('19950100109','i)Triangle AOP is a right-angled triangle.;  $$\\frac{AP}{OA} = \\tan  0.4$$;  = $$10 \\tan  0.4$$; = 4.228m;Perimeter of shaded region = arc AB + 2(AP);  = 10(0.8) + 2(4.228)m; = 16.5m ;ii)	Area of Triangle AOP = $$\\frac{1}{2}(\\frac{OA}{AP})$$  = $$\\frac{1}{2} (10)(4.228)m^2$$;=$$21.14m^2$$ ;Area of shaded region = 2(area of triangle AOP) - area of sector AOB; = $$2(21.14) - 0.5(10)^2(0.8)$$;  = $$2.28m^2$$;'),
