('20100300109','For $$3x^2-2x+1=0$$ with roots $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$,;Sum of roots: $$\\alpha  + \\beta  = \\frac{2}{3}$$;Products of roots: $$\\alpha  \\beta  = \\frac{1}{3}$$;For the quadratic equations with roots $$\\alpha  + 2\\beta $$ and $$2\\alpha +\\beta $$,;Sum of roots ;= $$(\\alpha  + 2\\beta ) + (2\\alpha  + \\beta )$$;=$$3\\alpha  + 3\\beta $$;= $$3(\\alpha  + \\beta )$$;= $$3(\\frac{2}{3})$$;= 2;;Products of roots ;=$$(\\alpha  +2\\beta )(2\\alpha  + \\beta )$$;= $$2\\alpha ^2 +\\alpha  \\beta  + 4\\alpha  \\beta  + 2 \\beta ^2$$ ;= $$2[\\alpha ^2+2 \\alpha  \\beta  + \\beta ^2] + \\alpha  \\beta $$;= $$2(\\alpha  + \\beta )^2 + \\alpha  \\beta $$;= $$2(\\frac{2}{3})^2 + \\frac{1}{3}$$;= $$\\frac{11}{9}$$;Hence quadratic equation with roots $$\\alpha +2\\beta $$ and $$2\\alpha  + \\beta $$:;$$x^2$$ -(Sum of roots)x + (Products of roots) =0;$$x^2-(2)x+\\frac{11}{9} =0$$;$$9x^2-18x+11=0$$ (ANS)'),
