(273,'Integration_By_Reverse_Of_Differentiation','F',49,'Integration - If $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x} [F(x)] = f(x)$$, then $$\\int f(x) dx = F(x) + c$$ where $$c$$ is a constant.'),
